works.description: Musical instrument auction house Tarisio, which sold an Antonio Stradivari violin in 2010 for record-breaking $3.6 million, will offer the Lady Blunt Stradivarius violin of 1721 at their June 20, 2011 online auction. Built in 1721 by Antonio Stradivari, the Lady Blunt violin is being sold by the Nippon Music Foundation, with all the proceeds benefitting their Northeastern Japan Earthquake and Tsunami Relief Fund.
